### VLAN and Network Creation

- [ ] Log into UniFi at [{{ platforms.gateway.url }}]({{ platforms.gateway.url }})

> **Note:** DNS servers ({{ vms.dns1_prod.ip }}, {{ vms.dns2_prod.ip }}) are not
> running yet. DHCP will advertise them, but DNS resolution won't work until DNS
> VMs are deployed in Step 3 of the implementation plan.

#### Prod Network (VLAN {{ environments.prod.vlan_id }})

- [ ] Navigate to **Settings** → **Networks** → **Create New Network**
- [ ] Configure:

| Field | Value |
|-------|-------|
| Name | Prod |
| VLAN ID | {{ environments.prod.vlan_id }} |
| Gateway IP/Subnet | {{ environments.prod.gateway }}/{{ environments.prod.subnet | cidr_prefix }} |
| DHCP Mode | DHCP Server |
| DHCP Range | {{ environments.prod.subnet | subnet_ip(100) }} – {{ environments.prod.subnet | subnet_ip(254) }} |
| DHCP DNS Server | {{ vms.dns1_prod.ip }}, {{ vms.dns2_prod.ip }} |
| DHCP Search Domain | {{ environments.prod.dns_domain }} |

- [ ] **DHCP DNS servers** — set to the per-environment DNS server IPs, NOT the gateway:
  - DNS Server 1: `{{ vms.dns1_prod.ip }}` (dns1-prod)
  - DNS Server 2: `{{ vms.dns2_prod.ip }}` (dns2-prod)

  > **UI path (UniFi Network {{ platforms.gateway.version | default('10.x') }}):**
  > **Settings → Networks → Prod → DHCP → DHCP Service Management →**
  > scroll down to **DNS Server** and switch from "Auto" to "Manual", then
  > enter the two DNS server IPs above.

  > **WARNING:** Do NOT leave DNS set to "Auto" or use the gateway IP
  > (`{{ environments.prod.gateway }}`). The gateway does not serve the
  > per-environment DNS zones. VMs would fail to resolve internal hostnames
  > like `influxdb.prod.{{ domain }}` and unqualified names like `influxdb`
  > would not resolve at all. This is the setting that makes
  > `dig +search vault` from inside a VM resolve to the correct
  > per-environment IP.

- [ ] Save

